<br>
Lord Rak'Ashiir was the leader of the CoM back before it was a lost city...It was he that brought the shadow down upon his people.  You see...the iksar here worshiped Cazic-Thule...and one night, CT snuck down and stole Rak's child.  Rak went insane and denounced Cazic.  Neh'Ashiir was Rak'Ashiir's wife.  and she fell in love with High Scale Kirn...the high priest of the temple of CoM.  They had an affair.  When you investigate and try to find what happens, you have to go to High Scale Kirn (who died on a crusade of sorts in the Hole) and hand him the 'icon of the high scale' which was left by accident in Neh'ashiir's bed chamber and was carried out by servant...who gossip'd about it and it got written down by a historian who's books you find previous to bringing the icon to Kirn.  <br>
<br>
Kirn is wearing a promise ring from Neh.  handing him the Icon enrages him and yells that you'll have to destroy him to get the proof.  so you do, and loot the ring.  This you bring to Neh'Ashiir as proof of her infidelity to Rak and her aid in bringing about the loss of the city's faith.  <br>
<br>
Here's the kicker.  you give Neh the ring...and she goes crazy and says that everything is lost and she has nothing to live for but she'll destroy you if she can.  so... I was with Korwynn when he killed Neh'Ashiir.  and NEH'ASHIIR IS A MAN BABY!  How could they mess that up so bad?!  SHE HAS A FRIGGING KID! I wanted to make sure because I wasn't positive Neh was male from the look, so i went up and did /dance.  Ortaak grabs ahold of Neh'Ashiir and begins to dance with him.  /sigh.  I think i'll petition when I kill Neh for my epic...that's just wrong.  <br>
<br>
